    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-08-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-08-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="322" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <head>No. 322.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Phelps</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-08-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">August</hi> 2, 1887</date>.
                            (Received August 13.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                        your instruction of the 12th ultimo, inclosing two copies of your “proposal
                        for an arrangement,” with the Canadian “observations” and your reply thereto
                        printed in parallel columns, and to inform you that I have communicated a
                        copy of the same to Lord Salisbury.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">E. J. Phelps.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
